161
00:06:30,230 --> 00:06:31,310
Joel Neatrour,

162
00:06:31,310 --> 00:06:36,479
“Hey Chris: how will China reconcile its
suppression / oppression

163
00:06:36,479 --> 00:06:40,979
of Chinese Uyghurs diplomatically with Saudi
Arabia and Iran?

164
00:06:40,979 --> 00:06:42,880
Surely that is, or will become,

165
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:45,710
a bone of contention in the budding relationship

166
00:06:45,710 --> 00:06:48,169
between the CCP and key players in the Middle
East.”

167
00:06:48,169 --> 00:06:51,599
That’s a question a lot of people have been
asking.

168
00:06:51,599 --> 00:06:53,990
The Chinese Communist Party is brutally oppressing

169
00:06:53,990 --> 00:06:58,389
the mostly Muslim ethnic Uighur population
in China’s Xinjiang.

170
00:06:58,389 --> 00:07:01,550
Including most likely killing them for their
organs.

171
00:07:01,550 --> 00:07:03,419
But there’s been hardly any complaints

172
00:07:03,419 --> 00:07:06,789
from any of the predominantly Muslim Middle
Eastern countries.

173
00:07:06,789 --> 00:07:07,789
Why?

174
00:07:07,789 --> 00:07:10,250
Well, I can’t say for sure.

175
00:07:10,250 --> 00:07:14,139
But China has been investing heavily in the
region.

176
00:07:14,139 --> 00:07:17,540
After a recent 28 billion dollar deal with
China,

177
00:07:17,540 --> 00:07:20,979
the Saudi Crown Prince did bring up the Uighurs,
saying

178
00:07:20,979 --> 00:07:24,139
“China has the right to carry out anti-terrorism

179
00:07:24,139 --> 00:07:27,449
and de-extremisation work for its national
security.”

180
00:07:27,449 --> 00:07:28,639
In fact so far,

181
00:07:28,639 --> 00:07:31,919
only Turkey has brought up the plight of the
Uighurs.

182
00:07:31,919 --> 00:07:33,419
And barely, at that.

183
00:07:33,419 --> 00:07:34,419
So I really have to wonder

184
00:07:34,419 --> 00:07:36,780
if China’s treatment of Muslims in China

185
00:07:36,780 --> 00:07:38,560
really is that big of a concern

186
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,840
for countries in the Middle East.

187
